title: The Good, the Bad, and the Bogus
description: Captain Harris bungles an operation to catch the Clown Gang and his punishment is to return to the police academy and train new recruits. His favorite grads also return, along with the Clown Gang, who become his new recruits.

title: Puttin' on the Dogs
description: To stop a number of cat burglaries, Lassard brings a new squad in to save the day, the K-9 Corps.

title: The Phantom of the Precinct
description: Officers begin to take extended leave because they fear the Phantom. Harris puts Mahoney and his gang on the case.

title: Cops and Robots
description: Harris wants to replace Mahoney and his gang with the Professor's new robot officers.

title: Police Academy Blues
description: Lassard is forced to step down at the academy and Captain Harris becomes his replacement. Mahoney and the gang then set out to get Lassard reinstated.

title: A Blue Knight at the Opera
description: The Academy is assigned to look after opera singer Mademoiselle Diva after several attempts have been made on her life.

title: Worth Her Weight in Gold
description: Unbeatable lady wrestler Amazona is on a crime spree in her free time. Sweetchuck offers to go undercover at her gym because he's fallen head over heels in love with her.

title: For Whom the Wedding Bells Toll
description: The Academy are assigned an undercover security mission at the wedding ceremony of a billionaire's daughter.

title: Westward Ho Hooks
description: Feeling unappreciated at the Academy, Sergeant Hooks finds a new job as the sheriff of a town being menaced by an outlaw gang.

title: My Mummy Lies Over the Ocean
K-9 Corps and the Peking Pooch
Now You Steal It, Now You Don't
Survival of the Fattest
description: The Academy cadets try to protect guest stars The Fat Boys from a deranged fan.
